# Feature file for Section 8.3: Ability Keywords
# Reference: Flesh and Blood Comprehensive Rules Section 8.3
#
# 8.3.1 Attack
#   Attack is a static ability. A layer with the attack ability is an attack-proxy.
#   8.3.1a When an attack-proxy resolves on the stack, it and its source move onto the
#           combat chain as a chain link.
#   8.3.1b If an attack-proxy is added to the stack, the combat chain opens (if it is
#           closed) and the Layer Step of combat begins.
#   8.3.1c To add an attack-proxy onto the stack, a legal attackable target must be
#           declared as the target of the attack.
#
# 8.3.2 Battleworn
#   Battleworn is a triggered-static ability that means "When the combat chain closes,
#   if this defended, put a -1{d} counter on it."
#
# 8.3.3 Blade Break
#   Blade Break is a triggered-static ability that means "When the combat chain closes,
#   if this defended, destroy it."
#
# 8.3.4 Dominate
#   Dominate is a static ability that means "This can't be defended by more than one
#   card from hand."
#   8.3.4a If an attack with dominate is currently defended by a card from hand, an
#           additional card cannot be added as a defending card if the card comes from
#           a player's hand.
#   8.3.4b If an attack with dominate is currently defended by a card from hand on the
#           activate chain link, defense reaction cards cannot be played from hand.
#   8.3.4c If an attack is defended by two or more cards from hand and then the attack
#           gains dominate, no cards are retroactively removed from defending.
#
# 8.3.5 Go again
#   Go again is a special resolution ability that means "Gain 1 action point."
#   8.3.5a If go again is an ability of a non-attack layer on the stack, the controlling
#           player gains 1 action point after all other resolution abilities have resolved.
#   8.3.5b If go again is an ability of an attack on the active chain link, the controlling
#           player gains 1 action point at the beginning of the Resolution Step of combat.
#   8.3.5c An object cannot have more than one "go again" ability. If an effect would give
#           the "go again" ability to an object that already has it, that part fails.
#
# 8.3.6 Legendary
#   Legendary is a meta-static ability that means "You may only have 1 of this in your
#   constructed deck."
#
# 8.3.7 Specialization
#   Specialization is a meta-static ability. Specialization is written as "[HERO]
#   Specialization" which means "You may only have this in your deck if your hero is
#   [HERO]."
#
# 8.3.8 Arcane Barrier
#   Arcane Barrier is a static ability written as "Arcane Barrier N" which means "If you
#   would be dealt arcane damage, you may pay N{r} to prevent N of that damage."
#
# 8.3.9 Boost
#   Boost is an optional additional-cost play-static ability that means "As an additional
#   cost to play this, you may banish the top card of your deck. If you do, if it's a
#   Mechanologist card, this gets go again."
#   8.3.9a If a player pays the additional cost, the player is considered to have boosted,
#           even if the banished card is not a Mechanologist card.
#   8.3.9b A player cannot boost if they cannot pay the additional cost.
#
# 8.3.10 Temper
#   Temper is a triggered-static ability that means "When the combat chain closes, if this
#   defended, put a -1{d} counter on it, then destroy it if it has zero {d}."
#
# 8.3.11 Blood Debt
#   Blood debt is a triggered-static ability. Blood debt means "While this is in your
#   banished zone, at the beginning of your end phase, lose 1{h}."
#   8.3.11a Blood debt only triggers if its source is public in the banished zone at the
#            beginning of the owner's end phase.
#
# 8.3.13 Phantasm
#   Phantasm is a triggered-static ability that means "Whenever this is defended by a
#   non-Illusionist attack action card with 6 or more {p}, destroy this."
#   8.3.13a The state-condition is met if defender is non-Illusionist attack action card
#            with power 6+; triggered-layer is put on stack and resolves to destroy attack.
#   8.3.13b If an attack is destroyed by phantasm before damage is calculated, the combat
#            chain closes. If destroyed after damage is calculated, it does not close.
#
# 8.3.14 Spectra
#   Spectra is a static ability and a triggered-static ability that mean "this can be
#   attacked" and "When this becomes the target of an attack, destroy this."
#   8.3.14a An object with Spectra can be the target of an attack, even if not living.
#   8.3.14b When an object with Spectra becomes the target of an attack, a triggered-layer
#            is put on the stack and when it resolves, the Spectra object is destroyed. If
#            there are no other legal attack-targets, the combat chain closes.
#
# 8.3.15 Spellvoid
#   Spellvoid is a static ability written as "Spellvoid N" which means "If you would be
#   dealt arcane damage, you may destroy this to prevent N of that damage."
#   8.3.15a If the controlling player cannot destroy the object with Spellvoid, they
#            cannot apply the optional prevention effect.
#
# 8.3.16 Essence
#   Essence is a meta-static ability written as "Essence of [SUPERTYPES]" which means
#   "You may have [SUPERTYPES] cards in your deck, as though your hero had those supertypes."
#
# 8.3.17 Fusion
#   Fusion is an optional additional-cost play-static ability written as "[SUPERTYPES]
#   Fusion" which means "As an additional cost to play this, you may reveal (a/an)
#   [SUPERTYPES] card(s) from your hand."
#   8.3.17a If a player pays the cost, they are considered to have fused those supertypes.
#   8.3.17b A player cannot fuse if they cannot reveal the specified cards from hand.
#   8.3.17c A player may only reveal up to one card for each supertype. A single card may
#            count for multiple supertypes.
#   8.3.17d "and" requires revealing cards with all supertypes. "and/or" requires at least one.
#
# 8.3.18 Heave
#   Heave is a hidden triggered ability written as "Heave N" which means "While this is
#   in your hand, at the beginning of your end phase, you may pay N{r} and put this
#   face-up into your arsenal. If you do, create N Seismic Surge tokens."
#   8.3.18a If a player pays the cost, the player is considered to have heaved.
#   8.3.18b A player cannot heave if they cannot pay the cost or put the card into arsenal.
#
# 8.3.19 Quell
#   Quell is a static ability written as "Quell N" which means "If you would be dealt
#   damage, you may pay N{r} to prevent N of that damage. If you do, destroy this at
#   the beginning of the end phase."
#
# 8.3.20 Ward
#   Ward is a static ability written as "Ward N" which means "If you would be dealt
#   damage, destroy this to prevent N of that damage."
#
# 8.3.21 Ephemeral
#   Ephemeral is a meta-static ability and a static ability that mean "You can't start
#   the game with this in your deck" and "If this would be put into a graveyard from
#   anywhere, instead it ceases to exist."
#   8.3.21a A player cannot include a card with Ephemeral in their card-pool.
#   8.3.21b A card that ceases to exist from Ephemeral is removed from the game.
#
# 8.3.22 Overpower
#   Overpower is a static ability that means "This can't be defended by more than one
#   action card."
#   8.3.22a If an attack with overpower is currently defended by an action card, an
#            additional action card cannot be added as a defending card.
#   8.3.22b If an attack is defended by two or more action cards and then gains overpower,
#            no cards are retroactively removed.
#
# 8.3.23 Piercing
#   Piercing is a static ability written as "Piercing N" which means "If this is defended
#   by an equipment, it gets +N{p}."
#
# 8.3.24 Stealth
#   Stealth is an ability that means nothing.
#
# 8.3.25 Mirage
#   Mirage is a triggered-static ability that means "When this is defending a
#   non-Illusionist attack with 6 or more {p}, destroy this."
#
# 8.3.26 Pairs [with OBJECT]
#   Pairs is a static ability that means "Equip this only with an OBJECT."
#   8.3.26a A card with pairs can only be equipped if the player already has an OBJECT
#            equipped, or if an OBJECT is being equipped as part of the same event.
#
# 8.3.27 Rune Gate
#   Rune Gate is a play-static ability that means "If you control Runechants >= this's
#   {r} cost, you may play it from your banished zone without paying its {r} cost."
#   8.3.27a If a player plays from banished using rune gate, they are considered to have
#            rune gated.
#
# 8.3.28 Ambush
#   Ambush is a while-static ability that means "While this is in your arsenal, you may
#   defend with it."
#
# 8.3.29 Crank
#   Crank is a static ability that means "As this enters the arena, you may remove a
#   steam counter from it. If you do, gain an action point."
#   8.3.29a If a player removes a steam counter using crank, they are considered to have
#            cranked.
#
# 8.3.30 Modular
#   Modular is a static ability that means "This may be equipped to any of your equipment
#   zones. It has the subtype of the zone it's equipped to."
#   8.3.30a The equipment zones are Arms, Chest, Head, and Legs.
#   8.3.30b A card can only be equipped to its owner's equipment zones with Modular.
#   8.3.30c A card with modular does not have any equipment subtypes until equipped.
#
# 8.3.31 Protect
#   Protect is a static ability that means "You may defend any hero attacked by an
#   opponent with this."
#   8.3.31a If a player defends with a card with protect, they and the card are considered
#            to have protected.
#
# 8.3.32 Scrap
#   Scrap is a play-static ability that means "As an additional cost to play this, you
#   may banish an item or equipment from your graveyard."
#   8.3.32a If a player pays the cost, they are considered to have scrapped.
#   8.3.32b A player cannot scrap if they cannot banish an item or equipment from graveyard.
#
# 8.3.33 Beat Chest
#   Beat Chest is a play-static ability that means "As an additional cost to play this,
#   you may discard a card with 6 or more {p}."
#   8.3.33a If a player pays the cost, they are considered to have beaten chest.
#   8.3.33b A player cannot beat chest if they cannot discard a card with 6+ {p}.
#
# 8.3.34 Guardwell
#   Guardwell is a static ability that means "When the combat chain closes, if this
#   defended, put -1{d} counters on it equal to its {d}."
#
# 8.3.35 Universal
#   Universal is a while-static ability that means "While in any zone, it is the same
#   class as your hero."
#
# 8.3.36 Cloaked
#   Cloaked is a static ability that means "Equip this face-down."
#
# 8.3.37 Arcane Shelter
#   Arcane Shelter is a static ability written as "Arcane Shelter N" which means "If you
#   would be dealt arcane damage, destroy this to prevent N of that damage."
#
# 8.3.38 Meld
#   Meld is a static ability that means "You may pay twice the base cost of this to play
#   both halves of this."
#   8.3.38a If a player pays the alternative cost, the card is considered melded.
#   8.3.38b Meld sets the asset-cost before increases/decreases are applied.
#   8.3.38c A melded card has properties of both sides on a split-card.
#
# 8.3.39 Perched
#   Perched is a static ability that means "This can be equipped in addition to a 2H
#   weapon. This can't be attacked while it's equipped."
#   8.3.39a A card with perched may be equipped to a weapon zone a two-hander occupies
#            but does not occupy; otherwise requires an empty zone.
#   8.3.39b A card with perched cannot be equipped unless it has a qualifying subtype.
#   8.3.39c An equipped card with perched cannot be the target of an attack.
#
# 8.3.40 Unlimited
#   Unlimited is a meta-static ability that means "You may have any number of this card
#   in your deck."
#
# 8.3.41 Watery Grave
#   Watery Grave is a triggered-static ability that means "When this is put into your
#   graveyard from the arena, turn it face-down."
#
# 8.3.42 Suspense
#   Suspense is a static ability and two triggered-static abilities that mean: "This
#   enters the arena with 2 suspense counters," "At the start of your turn, remove a
#   suspense counter from this," and "When this has no suspense counters, destroy it."

Feature: Section 8.3 - Ability Keywords
    As a game engine
    I need to correctly implement ability keywords
    So that cards with special abilities function according to the rules

    # ===== 8.3.1 Attack =====

    Scenario: Attack keyword makes a layer an attack-proxy
        Given a card has the attack keyword ability
        Then that card's layer is an attack-proxy

    Scenario: Playing an attack opens the combat chain
        Given the combat chain is closed
        And a player has an attack card in hand
        When the player plays the attack card
        Then the combat chain opens
        And the Layer Step of combat begins

    Scenario: Attacking requires a legal attackable target
        Given a player has an attack card in hand
        When the player attempts to play the attack without declaring a target
        Then the action is illegal

    Scenario: Attack-proxy moves to combat chain on resolution
        Given an attack-proxy is on the stack
        When the attack-proxy resolves
        Then it and its source move onto the combat chain as a chain link

    # ===== 8.3.2 Battleworn =====

    Scenario: Battleworn puts a minus defense counter when defending closes chain
        Given a piece of equipment has battleworn
        And the equipment defended this combat chain
        When the combat chain closes
        Then a -1 defense counter is placed on the equipment

    Scenario: Battleworn does not trigger if equipment did not defend
        Given a piece of equipment has battleworn
        And the equipment did not defend this combat chain
        When the combat chain closes
        Then no -1 defense counter is placed on the equipment from battleworn

    # ===== 8.3.3 Blade Break =====

    Scenario: Blade Break destroys equipment when defending closes chain
        Given a piece of equipment has blade break
        And the equipment defended this combat chain
        When the combat chain closes
        Then the equipment is destroyed

    Scenario: Blade Break does not trigger if equipment did not defend
        Given a piece of equipment has blade break
        And the equipment did not defend this combat chain
        When the combat chain closes
        Then the equipment is not destroyed by blade break

    # ===== 8.3.4 Dominate =====

    Scenario: Dominate prevents a second hand card from defending
        Given an attacking card has dominate
        And the defending player has already defended with one card from hand
        When the defending player attempts to add a second card from hand as a defender
        Then the additional defense is not allowed

    Scenario: Dominate prevents defense reactions from hand when defended by hand card
        Given an attacking card has dominate
        And the defending player has defended with a card from hand on the active chain link
        When the defending player attempts to play a defense reaction from hand
        Then the defense reaction play is not allowed

    Scenario: Dominate does not retroactively remove defenders added before it was gained
        Given an attack was defended by two cards from hand
        When the attack gains dominate after the defenses were added
        Then neither defending card is removed

    Scenario: Dominate does not restrict defense from non-hand sources
        Given an attacking card has dominate
        And the defending player has already defended with one card from hand
        When the defending player adds a card from their arsenal as a defender
        Then the arsenal defense is allowed

    # ===== 8.3.5 Go again =====

    Scenario: Go again on non-attack layer grants action point after resolution
        Given a non-attack card with go again is on the stack
        When the non-attack card resolves
        Then the controlling player gains 1 action point
        And the action point is granted after all other resolution abilities resolve

    Scenario: Go again on attack grants action point at start of Resolution Step
        Given an attack with go again is the active chain link
        When the Resolution Step of combat begins
        Then the controlling player gains 1 action point

    Scenario: Go again cannot be duplicated on the same object
        Given a card already has the go again ability
        When an effect attempts to give go again to that card
        Then that part of the effect fails

    # ===== 8.3.6 Legendary =====

    Scenario: Legendary limits deck to one copy in constructed
        Given a card has the legendary keyword
        When a player tries to include two copies in their constructed deck
        Then only one copy is allowed

    # ===== 8.3.7 Specialization =====

    Scenario: Specialization requires matching hero in deck
        Given a card has Dorinthea Specialization
        And a player's hero is not Dorinthea
        When the player attempts to include the card in their deck
        Then the card is not allowed in the deck

    Scenario: Specialization allows card in deck when hero matches
        Given a card has Dorinthea Specialization
        And a player's hero is Dorinthea
        When the player includes the card in their deck
        Then the card is allowed in the deck

    # ===== 8.3.8 Arcane Barrier =====

    Scenario: Arcane Barrier can prevent arcane damage by paying resource cost
        Given a player has an object with Arcane Barrier 2
        When the player would be dealt 5 arcane damage
        And the player pays 2 resource points to activate Arcane Barrier
        Then 2 arcane damage is prevented

    Scenario: Arcane Barrier is optional
        Given a player has an object with Arcane Barrier 2
        When the player would be dealt arcane damage
        And the player chooses not to pay the Arcane Barrier cost
        Then the full arcane damage is dealt

    # ===== 8.3.9 Boost =====

    Scenario: Boost banishes top card of deck as additional cost
        Given a card has boost
        When a player plays the card and pays the boost cost
        Then the top card of their deck is banished
        And the player is considered to have boosted

    Scenario: Boost grants go again if banished card is Mechanologist
        Given a card has boost
        When a player boosts and the banished card is a Mechanologist card
        Then the played card gets go again

    Scenario: Boost does not grant go again for non-Mechanologist card
        Given a card has boost
        When a player boosts and the banished card is not a Mechanologist card
        Then the played card does not get go again from boost
        And the player is still considered to have boosted

    Scenario: Player cannot boost if they have no cards in deck
        Given a card has boost
        And a player's deck is empty
        When the player attempts to play the card with the boost cost
        Then the boost additional cost cannot be paid

    # ===== 8.3.10 Temper =====

    Scenario: Temper puts minus defense counter and destroys at zero defense
        Given a piece of equipment has temper with 1 defense remaining
        And the equipment defended this combat chain
        When the combat chain closes
        Then a -1 defense counter is placed on the equipment
        And the equipment is destroyed because it has zero defense

    Scenario: Temper puts minus defense counter without destroying when defense remains
        Given a piece of equipment has temper with 2 defense remaining
        And the equipment defended this combat chain
        When the combat chain closes
        Then a -1 defense counter is placed on the equipment
        And the equipment is not destroyed because it has defense remaining

    # ===== 8.3.11 Blood Debt =====

    Scenario: Blood Debt causes life loss at beginning of owner's end phase
        Given a card with blood debt is in the public banished zone
        When the beginning of the owner's end phase occurs
        Then the owner loses 1 life from blood debt

    Scenario: Blood Debt does not trigger if card is face-down in banished zone
        Given a card with blood debt is face-down in the banished zone
        When the beginning of the owner's end phase occurs
        Then no life is lost from blood debt

    Scenario: Blood Debt does not trigger if card is not in banished zone
        Given a card with blood debt is in the graveyard
        When the beginning of the owner's end phase occurs
        Then no life is lost from blood debt

    # ===== 8.3.13 Phantasm =====

    Scenario: Phantasm attack is destroyed when defended by non-Illusionist 6+ power card
        Given an attacking card has phantasm
        When it is defended by a non-Illusionist attack action card with 6 or more power
        Then a triggered-layer is put on the stack to destroy the phantasm attack

    Scenario: Phantasm triggered-layer resolves to destroy the attack
        Given an attacking card with phantasm has a destroy triggered-layer on the stack
        And the trigger condition is still met
        When the triggered-layer resolves
        Then the phantasm attack is destroyed

    Scenario: Phantasm destruction before damage closes the combat chain
        Given a phantasm attack is destroyed before damage is calculated
        When phantasm destroys the attack
        Then the combat chain closes

    Scenario: Phantasm destruction after damage does not close the combat chain
        Given a phantasm attack is destroyed after damage is calculated
        When phantasm destroys the attack
        Then the combat chain does not close due to phantasm

    Scenario: Phantasm does not trigger when defended by Illusionist attack card
        Given an attacking card has phantasm
        When it is defended by an Illusionist attack action card with 6 or more power
        Then phantasm does not trigger

    # ===== 8.3.14 Spectra =====

    Scenario: Spectra allows non-living object to be targeted by attacks
        Given a non-living permanent has spectra
        When a player attempts to target it with an attack
        Then the non-living object is a valid attack target

    Scenario: Spectra object is destroyed when it becomes target of attack
        Given a permanent has spectra
        When it becomes the target of an attack
        Then a triggered-layer is put on the stack to destroy the spectra object

    Scenario: Spectra destruction closes combat chain if no other legal targets
        Given a permanent with spectra was targeted by an attack
        And there are no other legal attack targets
        When the spectra triggered-layer resolves and destroys the object
        Then the combat chain closes

    # ===== 8.3.15 Spellvoid =====

    Scenario: Spellvoid allows destroying the object to prevent arcane damage
        Given a player has an object with Spellvoid 3
        When the player would be dealt arcane damage
        And the player chooses to activate Spellvoid
        Then the object is destroyed
        And 3 arcane damage is prevented

    Scenario: Spellvoid cannot be used if the object cannot be destroyed
        Given a player has an object with Spellvoid 3 that cannot be destroyed
        When the player would be dealt arcane damage
        Then the player cannot apply the Spellvoid prevention effect

    # ===== 8.3.16 Essence =====

    Scenario: Essence allows including supertype cards in deck
        Given a hero card has Essence of Earth
        When a player includes Earth cards in their deck
        Then the Earth cards are allowed as if the hero had the Earth supertype

    # ===== 8.3.17 Fusion =====

    Scenario: Fusion allows revealing supertype cards from hand as additional cost
        Given a card has Lightning Fusion
        And a player has a Lightning card in hand
        When the player plays the card and reveals the Lightning card for the fusion cost
        Then the player is considered to have fused Lightning

    Scenario: Fusion cannot be paid if no matching supertype card in hand
        Given a card has Lightning Fusion
        And a player has no Lightning cards in hand
        When the player attempts to pay the fusion cost
        Then the fusion additional cost cannot be paid

    Scenario: Fusion with "and" requires revealing cards for all listed supertypes
        Given a card has Earth and Lightning Fusion
        And a player has an Earth card but no Lightning card in hand
        When the player attempts to pay the fusion cost
        Then the fusion cannot be paid because not all required supertypes can be revealed

    Scenario: Fusion with "and/or" requires at least one matching supertype card
        Given a card has Earth and/or Lightning Fusion
        And a player has only an Earth card in hand
        When the player attempts to pay the fusion cost with the Earth card
        Then the fusion can be paid

    Scenario: Single card can satisfy multiple supertype requirements for fusion
        Given a card has Earth and/or Lightning Fusion
        And a player has a card that has both Earth and Lightning supertypes
        When the player reveals that single card for fusion
        Then it satisfies both supertype requirements

    # ===== 8.3.18 Heave =====

    Scenario: Heave allows moving card from hand to arsenal at end phase
        Given a card in hand has Heave 2
        And a player has 2 or more resource points
        When the beginning of the end phase occurs
        And the player pays the heave cost
        Then the card is placed face-up in the arsenal
        And 2 Seismic Surge tokens are created
        And the player is considered to have heaved

    Scenario: Heave cannot be activated without sufficient resources
        Given a card in hand has Heave 2
        And a player has only 1 resource point
        When the beginning of the end phase occurs
        Then the player cannot pay the heave cost

    # ===== 8.3.19 Quell =====

    Scenario: Quell prevents damage by paying resource cost
        Given a permanent has Quell 2
        When the permanent's controller would be dealt damage
        And the controller pays 2 resource points to activate Quell
        Then 2 damage is prevented
        And the permanent is destroyed at the beginning of the end phase

    # ===== 8.3.20 Ward =====

    Scenario: Ward prevents damage by destroying itself
        Given a permanent has Ward 3
        When the permanent's controller would be dealt damage
        And the controller activates Ward
        Then the permanent is destroyed
        And 3 damage is prevented

    # ===== 8.3.21 Ephemeral =====

    Scenario: Ephemeral card cannot be included in card-pool
        Given a card has the ephemeral keyword
        When a player attempts to include the card in their card-pool
        Then the card is not allowed in the card-pool

    Scenario: Ephemeral card ceases to exist instead of going to graveyard
        Given a card with ephemeral would be put into the graveyard
        When the card would enter the graveyard
        Then the card ceases to exist instead
        And the card is removed from the game

    # ===== 8.3.22 Overpower =====

    Scenario: Overpower prevents a second action card from defending
        Given an attacking card has overpower
        And the defending player has already defended with one action card
        When the defending player attempts to add a second action card as a defender
        Then the second action card defense is not allowed

    Scenario: Overpower does not retroactively remove action card defenders added before it was gained
        Given an attack was defended by two action cards
        When the attack gains overpower after the defenses were added
        Then neither defending action card is removed

    # ===== 8.3.23 Piercing =====

    Scenario: Piercing increases attack power when defended by equipment
        Given an attacking card has Piercing 2
        When the attack is defended by an equipment
        Then the attack gets +2 power

    Scenario: Piercing does not increase power when not defended by equipment
        Given an attacking card has Piercing 2
        When the attack is defended by a card that is not equipment
        Then the attack power is not increased by piercing

    # ===== 8.3.25 Mirage =====

    Scenario: Mirage is destroyed when defending a non-Illusionist attack with 6 or more power
        Given a defending card has mirage
        When it is defending a non-Illusionist attack with 6 or more power
        Then the mirage card is destroyed

    Scenario: Mirage does not trigger when defending an Illusionist attack
        Given a defending card has mirage
        When it is defending an Illusionist attack with 6 or more power
        Then mirage does not trigger

    # ===== 8.3.26 Pairs =====

    Scenario: Pairs restricts equipping to only when the paired object is present
        Given a card has Pairs with Dawnblade
        And the player does not have Dawnblade equipped
        When the player attempts to equip the card
        Then the equipment is not allowed without the paired object

    Scenario: Pairs allows equipping when the paired object is being equipped simultaneously
        Given a card has Pairs with Dawnblade
        And Dawnblade is being equipped as part of the same event
        When both cards are equipped together
        Then the pairs card can be equipped

    # ===== 8.3.27 Rune Gate =====

    Scenario: Rune Gate allows playing from banished zone when Runechants meet cost
        Given a card with Rune Gate and cost 3 is in the banished zone
        And a player controls 3 or more Runechants
        When the player plays the card using rune gate
        Then the card is played without paying the resource cost
        And the player is considered to have rune gated

    Scenario: Rune Gate cannot be used if Runechants are fewer than the cost
        Given a card with Rune Gate and cost 3 is in the banished zone
        And a player controls only 2 Runechants
        When the player attempts to use rune gate
        Then rune gate cannot be activated

    # ===== 8.3.28 Ambush =====

    Scenario: Ambush allows defending with a card from arsenal
        Given a card with ambush is in a player's arsenal
        When an opponent's attack resolves and the player defends
        Then the player can use the ambush card from arsenal to defend

    # ===== 8.3.29 Crank =====

    Scenario: Crank allows removing a steam counter for an action point on entering arena
        Given a card with crank enters the arena with a steam counter on it
        When the player removes the steam counter using crank
        Then the player gains 1 action point
        And the player is considered to have cranked

    # ===== 8.3.30 Modular =====

    Scenario: Modular allows equipping to any equipment zone
        Given a card has modular
        When the player equips it to their Head zone
        Then the card is equipped to the Head zone

    Scenario: Modular card gains the subtype of its equipped zone
        Given a card with modular is equipped to the Chest zone
        Then the card has the Chest equipment subtype

    Scenario: Modular card has no equipment subtype before equipping
        Given a card has modular and is not yet equipped
        Then the card has no equipment subtype

    Scenario: Modular only allows equipping to owner's zones
        Given a card has modular
        When a player attempts to equip the card to an opponent's equipment zone
        Then the equipment is not allowed

    # ===== 8.3.31 Protect =====

    Scenario: Protect allows defending an ally hero attacked by opponent
        Given a player has a card with protect
        And an opponent is attacking a different allied hero
        When the player uses the protect card to defend
        Then the defense is allowed
        And the player and card are considered to have protected

    # ===== 8.3.32 Scrap =====

    Scenario: Scrap allows banishing item or equipment from graveyard as additional cost
        Given a card has scrap
        And a player has an equipment card in their graveyard
        When the player plays the card and pays the scrap cost by banishing the equipment
        Then the equipment is banished from the graveyard
        And the player is considered to have scrapped

    Scenario: Scrap cannot be paid without an item or equipment in graveyard
        Given a card has scrap
        And a player's graveyard has no items or equipment
        When the player attempts to pay the scrap cost
        Then the scrap additional cost cannot be paid

    # ===== 8.3.33 Beat Chest =====

    Scenario: Beat Chest allows discarding a high-power card as additional cost
        Given a card has beat chest
        And a player has a card with 6 or more power in hand
        When the player plays the card and pays the beat chest cost
        Then the high-power card is discarded
        And the player is considered to have beaten chest

    Scenario: Beat Chest cannot be paid without a 6 or more power card in hand
        Given a card has beat chest
        And a player has no cards with 6 or more power in hand
        When the player attempts to pay the beat chest cost
        Then the beat chest additional cost cannot be paid

    # ===== 8.3.34 Guardwell =====

    Scenario: Guardwell puts minus defense counters equal to current defense when chain closes
        Given a permanent has guardwell with 3 current defense
        And the permanent defended this combat chain
        When the combat chain closes
        Then 3 minus-1-defense counters are placed on the permanent

    # ===== 8.3.35 Universal =====

    Scenario: Universal makes the card the same class as the hero in any zone
        Given a card has universal
        And the player's hero is a Ranger
        When the card is in the player's hand
        Then the card is considered to be a Ranger card

    # ===== 8.3.36 Cloaked =====

    Scenario: Cloaked requires equipping the card face-down
        Given a card has cloaked
        When the player equips the card
        Then the card is equipped face-down

    # ===== 8.3.37 Arcane Shelter =====

    Scenario: Arcane Shelter prevents arcane damage by destroying itself
        Given a player has an object with Arcane Shelter 2
        When the player would be dealt arcane damage
        And the player activates Arcane Shelter
        Then the object is destroyed
        And 2 arcane damage is prevented

    # ===== 8.3.38 Meld =====

    Scenario: Meld allows paying twice the base cost to play both halves of a split-card
        Given a split-card has meld with a base cost of 2
        When the player pays 4 resources to meld the card
        Then the card is considered melded
        And the card has properties of both sides

    Scenario: Meld cost is set before increases and decreases are applied
        Given a split-card has meld with a base cost of 2
        And there is a cost increase effect in play
        When the meld cost is calculated
        Then the meld alternative cost is set to 4 before increases are applied

    # ===== 8.3.39 Perched =====

    Scenario: Perched allows equipping alongside a two-handed weapon
        Given a player has a two-handed weapon equipped occupying one weapon zone
        And a card with perched has a valid equipment subtype
        When the player equips the perched card to the unoccupied weapon zone
        Then the perched card is equipped alongside the two-handed weapon

    Scenario: Perched card cannot be targeted by attacks while equipped
        Given a player has a card with perched equipped
        When an opponent attempts to target the perched card with an attack
        Then the perched card cannot be targeted by the attack

    Scenario: Perched card can be targeted by non-attack effects
        Given a player has a card with perched equipped
        When a non-attack effect targets the perched card
        Then the perched card is a valid target for the non-attack effect

    # ===== 8.3.40 Unlimited =====

    Scenario: Unlimited allows any number of copies in constructed deck
        Given a card has the unlimited keyword
        When a player includes 4 copies in their constructed deck
        Then all 4 copies are allowed

    # ===== 8.3.41 Watery Grave =====

    Scenario: Watery Grave turns card face-down when put into graveyard from arena
        Given a card in the arena has watery grave
        When the card is put into the graveyard from the arena
        Then the card is turned face-down in the graveyard

    Scenario: Watery Grave does not apply when card goes to graveyard from a non-arena source
        Given a card with watery grave is in hand
        When the card is put into the graveyard from hand
        Then the card is not turned face-down by watery grave

    # ===== 8.3.42 Suspense =====

    Scenario: Suspense causes card to enter arena with 2 suspense counters
        Given a card has suspense
        When the card enters the arena
        Then the card has 2 suspense counters on it

    Scenario: Suspense removes a counter at the start of each turn
        Given a card with suspense is in the arena with 2 suspense counters
        When the start of the controlling player's turn occurs
        Then one suspense counter is removed from the card

    Scenario: Suspense destroys the card when it has no counters remaining
        Given a card with suspense is in the arena with 1 suspense counter
        When the start of the controlling player's turn occurs
        Then the suspense counter is removed
        And the card is destroyed because it has no suspense counters
